-- Serbian chamber of commerce head to become economy minister-report
-- By Ivana Sekularac
-- Tue Aug 19, 2014 07:43AM EDT
-- None



BELGRADE, Aug 19 (Reuters) - Serbian Prime Minister Aleksandar Vucic will nominate the head of Serbia's Chamber of Commerce, Zeljko Sertic, as the Balkan country's economy minister, Serbian media reported on Tuesday.

Radio B92, citing sources, said Vucic would announce Sertic's nomination later in the day.